 boundaries, and choosing/rolling out models at scale (real org playbooks).

*Advanced Security: AI-assisted code scanning & code review* =E2=80=94 what=
=E2=80=99s new, how it changes triage/MTTR, and where it beats legacy SAST.

*Scaling Actions & Codespaces org-wide* =E2=80=94 patterns for monorepos, c=
ache stragegies, cost control, and developer-velocity metrics.

*Value Stream Management on GitHub* =E2=80=94 instrumenting flow metrics th=
at leadership actually cares about (lead time, deployment freq, change fail=
 rate).

--------------------------------------------
*EDU community highlights (image galleries)*
--------------------------------------------

Campus Experts kicked off Universe with a full community agenda=E2=80=94 *m=
eeting GitHub COO Kyle Daigle* , touring the *Golden Gate Bridge* and San F=
rancisco, getting a look inside the *GitHub office* , and joining *panels a=
nd discussions with Hubbers* about what=E2=80=99s next on campus.

The *Educator Lab Session* yesterday was hands-on and idea-dense=E2=80=94sh=
aring ways to *improve education products* , *discussing AI in education* ,=
 *collaborating on practical classroom workflows* , and capturing *take-hom=
e ideas* for the next term.

Behind the scenes, GitHub Education teamed up with volunteers to assemble t=
his year=E2=80=99s *programmable badges* =E2=80=94a small, tangible example=
 of the community effort that makes Universe run smoothly.

Whether you joined us live or plan to catch up later, we hope these highlig=
hts help you explore the latest in developer tools, security, and AI on Git=
Hub. All sessions will be available on demand=E2=80=94so you can dive in wh=
enever it works best for you.

